root.pub-comments: The classification presented here includes 'language chains', similar to the concept of dialect chains. This results in sub-groups that overlap each other, such that each language may appear in several different subgroups to reflect the intent of the author. "This overlap or 'sub-group chaining' goes some way towards resolving the problem of sharp cut-offs, see Wurm 1972. It is felt, too, that the 'sub-group chain' adopted in the classification presented below answers to a sociological reality" (Tryon 1976:81).
